cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CC

This paper discusses the challenges associated with deploying and optimizing big data applications and machine learning algorithms in cloud data centers and networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of big data applications, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of cloud computing infrastructures and related technologies, which makes cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible category as well.
